</para><quote depth="1"><quote depth="2"><quotepara depth="2">Anyway - that looks like a good patch.  I've been dying to get rid of all 
those silly make_nmb_name() calls everywhere but was not brave enough.
</quotepara></quote><quotepara depth="1">
I'll proabably add a cli_pipe_connection() function (feel free to suggest 
a better name) that just calls cli_full_connection, but with IPC$ implicit
and instead specifying the pipe to setup.

</quotepara><quotepara depth="1">How does that sound?
</quotepara></quote><para depth="0">
Sounds good to me.

</para><para depth="0">One point - is there any reason to pass around the password and the
length of the password to cli_full_connection()?

</para><para depth="0">Tim.
</para></body></message>